First of all, never use latest versions of the packages in your hackathon projects, may cost you a lot of time to waste.

How I fixed it?

I just had to add a loading state to my index page

```js
const { data: session, status } = useSession();


if (status === 'loading') {
    return (
      <div className="mx-auto grid place-content-center h-screen my-10">
        <Head>
          <title>Dashboard</title>
        </Head>
        <AiOutlineLoading className="text-white h-14 w-14 animate-spin" />
      </div>
    );
  }
```

But still there weren't any development errors, so the Next-Auth team may need to work on this.

Also the `getSession` hook only works in the server-side alongside `getServerSideProps`

